</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA83A22EB6FFFDFFF24EDF0FB53FF67" blockId="17.[151,1436,1877,2012]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1436,153,468]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="361" pageId="17" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6FFFDCFF24EDF0FE58F840" bold="true" box="[199,436,1985,2012]" pageId="17" pageNumber="360">Material examined:</emphasis>
four glued shells labelled “Dono Bellini” [Donated by Bellini] and “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C1741A1EB6FFFDCFB5CEDF3FA70F840" authority="Sta." authorityName="Sta." box="[1215,1436,1986,2012]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Helix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="17" pageNumber="361" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subprofuga" subGenus="Heliomanes">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6FFFDCFB5CEDF3FB10F840" box="[1215,1276,1986,2012]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="360">Helix</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6FFFDCFAEEEDF3FA7FF840" box="[1293,1427,1986,2012]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="360">Heliomanes</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFF74EAA8FEFAFF2F" box="[151,278,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">subprofuga</emphasis>
Sta.—(
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFE97EAA8FE0FFF2F" box="[372,483,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">Xerophila</emphasis>
)—Capri” and labelled by Bellini “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C1741A1EB6CFFDFFC6CEAA8FAF4FF2F" authority=", Stabile-Capri" authorityName="Stabile-Capri" box="[911,1304,153,179]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Helix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="18" pageNumber="361" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subprofuga">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFC6CEAA8FBB4FF2F" box="[911,1112,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">Helix subprofuga</emphasis>
, Stabile—Capri
</taxonomicName>
” (MZF2— Z6969); 18 shells labelled by Bellini “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C1741A1EB6CFFDFFDA8EA8FFC9BFF4B" box="[587,887,189,215]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Helix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="18" pageNumber="361" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subprofuga" subGenus="Xerophila">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFDA8EA8FFD8BFF4B" box="[587,615,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">H.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFD94EA8CFD0AFF4B" box="[631,742,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">Xerophila</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFD1BEA8CFC9BFF4B" box="[760,887,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">subprofuga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Stabile—juv.—Capri” (MCCIC—drawer 19, n. 297b). All these shells belong to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C1741A1EB6CFFDFFDD3EAD0FC14FF67" authority="(Rossmassler, 1837)" authorityName="Rossmassler" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Rossmassler" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[560,1016,225,251]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hygromiidae" genus="Cernuella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="18" pageNumber="361" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cisalpina">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFDD3EAD0FCE2FF67" box="[560,782,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">Cernuella cisalpina</emphasis>
(Rossmässler, 1837)
</taxonomicName>
species complex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30D69A9EB6CFFDFFF24EB34FE01FE48" pageId="18" pageNumber="361" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA83A22EB6CFFDFFF24EB34FE01FE48" blockId="18.[151,1436,153,468]" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFF24EB34FED1FE83" bold="true" box="[199,317,261,287]" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">Remarks:</emphasis>
having been instituted on the basis of insignificant morphological characteristics, we rank it infrasubspecific, and thus not available (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6CFFDFFDE8EB18FD7CFEDF" author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[523,656,297,323]" pageId="18" pageNumber="361" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 
<date id="FFA91CE2EB6CFFDFFD28EB18FCC7FEDF" box="[715,811,296,323]" pageId="18" pageNumber="361" value="1945-10-02">10.2, 45</date>
.5, 45.6, glossary). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6CFFDFFC1AEB18FB77FEDF" author="Alzona, C." box="[1017,1179,297,323]" pageId="18" pageNumber="361" pagination="1 - 433" refId="ref15337" refString="Alzona, C. (1971) Malacofauna Italica. Catalogo e bibliografia dei molluschi viventi, terrestri e d'acqua dolce. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali e del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Milano, 111, 1 - 433." type="journal article" year="1971">Alzona (1971)</bibRefCitation>
listed “ 
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFB12EB1BFAA6FEDF" box="[1265,1354,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">maxima</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6CFFDFFAB3EB18FF3DFEFB" author="Bellini, R." pageId="18" pageNumber="361" pagination="149 - 194" refId="ref15792" refString="Bellini, R. (1915) I molluschi extramarini dei dintorni di Napoli. Monografia sintetica. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, Series 2, 27, 149 - 194." type="journal article" year="1915">Bellini 1915</bibRefCitation>
” as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1741A1EB6CFFDFFE4BEB7CFC3FFEF4" authority="(Stabile, 1864)" authorityName="Stabile" authorityYear="1864" baseAuthorityName="Stabile" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[424,979,333,360]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicellidae" genus="Helicella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="18" pageNumber="361" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subprofuga" subGenus="Cernuella">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFE4BEB7CFDE3FEFB" box="[424,527,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">Helicella</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFDC3EB7CFD7CFEFB" box="[544,656,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">Cernuella</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFD41EB7CFCCDFEFB" box="[674,801,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">subprofuga</emphasis>
(Stabile, 1864)
</taxonomicName>
, now 
<taxonomicName id="4C1741A1EB6CFFDFFBFAEB7CFF37FE17" authority="(Rossmassler, 1837)" authorityName="Rossmassler" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Rossmassler" baseAuthorityYear="1837" class="Gastropoda" family="Hygromiidae" genus="Cernuella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="18" pageNumber="361" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cisalpina">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFBFAEB7CFB15FEFB" box="[1049,1273,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">Cernuella cisalpina</emphasis>
(Rossmässler, 1837)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6CFFDFFF0AEB40FDC0FE17" author="Manganelli, G. &amp; Giusti, F." box="[233,556,369,395]" pageId="18" pageNumber="361" refId="ref17747" refString="Manganelli, G. &amp; Giusti, F. (1988) Notulae malacologicae, XXXVIII. A new Hygromiidae from Italian Apennines and notes on the genus Cernuella and related taxa (Pulmonata: Helicoidea). Bollettino Malacologico, 23, 327 - 279." type="book" year="1988">Manganelli &amp; Giusti (1988)</bibRefCitation>
considered this taxon as belonging to the “small 
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFB8EEB40FB31FE17" box="[1133,1245,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">Cernuella</emphasis>
group”, with an uncertain identity. Specimens ascribed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1741A1EB6CFFDFFD8EEBA4FD19FE33" baseAuthorityName="Rossmassler" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[621,757,405,431]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hygromiidae" genus="Cernuella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="18" pageNumber="361" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cisalpina">
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFD8EEBA4FD19FE33" box="[621,757,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">C. cisalpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found again in Capri Island during recent field studies (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6CFFDFFF7CEB88FE75FE4F" author="Petraccioli, A. &amp; Barattolo, F. &amp; Crovato, P. &amp; Cretella, M. &amp; Maio, N. &amp; Aprea, G." box="[159,409,440,467]" pageId="18" pageNumber="361" pagination="19 - 48" refId="ref18257" refString="Petraccioli, A., Barattolo, F., Crovato, P., Cretella, M., Maio, N. &amp; Aprea, G. (2005) Guida pratica al riconoscimento dei macrogasteropodi terrestri attuali e fossili dell'Isola di Capri. Bollettino Sezione Campania ANISN, 29, 19 - 48." type="journal article" year="2005">
Petraccioli 
<emphasis id="B963E630EB6CFFDFFEFCEB8BFEB4FE4F" box="[287,344,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="361">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8647D3EB6CFFDFFE47EB88FE0DFE48" author="Petraccioli, A. &amp; Crovato, P. &amp; Cretella, M. &amp; Maio, N. &amp; Aprea, G. &amp; Barattolo, F." box="[420,481,441,468]" pageId="18" pageNumber="361" pagination="77 - 86" refId="ref18314" refString="Petraccioli, A., Crovato, P., Cretella, M., Maio, N., Aprea, G. &amp; Barattolo, F. (2006) I Gasteropodi continentali dell'Isola di Capri: risultati preliminari. In: Guglielmi, R. &amp; Nappi, A. (Eds.), La Natura in Campania: aspetti biotici e abiotici. Gruppo Attivo Campano A. R. C. A. - Onlus, Napoli, pp. 77 - 86." type="book chapter" year="2006">2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
